-- Bono, Sting, Gabriel Pay for Havel's Tapestry, CTK Says
-- B y   A n d r e a   D u d i k
-- 2012-11-21T07:14:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-21/bono-sting-gabriel-pay-for-havel-s-tapestry-ctk-says.html
U2’s Bono, The Edge, Sting, Peter
Gabriel and  Yoko Ono  paid 1.5 million koruna ($75,500) for a
tapestry dedicated to late Czech President  Vaclav Havel , CTK
news agency reported.  The tapestry, designed by Petr Sis, is to be unveiled Dec.
9 at Prague’s international airport that has been named after
Havel, who died last year, CTK said, citing Eva Krejci, the
airport’s spokeswoman.  Havel inspired these celebrities with his efforts to
promote human rights and freedom, CTK reported, citing comments
sent by Bono and The Edge to the airport regarding the tapestry.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Dudik in Prague at 
 adudikova@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
